In [[computational complexity theory]], a '''polynomial reduction''' is a [[reduction (complexity)|reduction]] of one problem to another that is performed in [[Time_complexity#Polynomial_time|polynomial time]]. A polynomial reduction takes polynomial time to pre-process inputs and post-process outputs. In such a reduction, the number of calls of the algorithm used to solve the problem being reduced also takes polynomial time.

